Package frc.team1711.swerve.util.odometry

Interface MovementManner.MovementSpeedSupplier

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Manner.SpeedSupplier
    Enclosing class:
    MovementManner
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.
    @FunctionalInterface
public static interface MovementManner.MovementSpeedSupplier
extends Manner.SpeedSupplier
    A functional interface which gets the speed the robot should move at given the distance that has yet to be traveled. An instance of this functional interface can be accessed from a given RobotMovement called movement through the following code: movement.getManner().getSpeedSupplier().
    See Also:
    TurnManner.TurnSpeedSupplier

      • speedWithSlowdown

        static MovementManner.MovementSpeedSupplier speedWithSlowdown​(double maxSpeed,
                                                              double slowdownDistance,
                                                              double minSpeed)
        Returns a MovementManner.MovementSpeedSupplier representing a speed that slows down after a certain distance to the autonomous endpoint, until a minimum speed is hit. That is, this type of MovementManner.MovementSpeedSupplier will return a given default (maximum) speed up until the robot must slow down (the slowdown distance). Then, when the robot is closer to the endpoint than this distance, the robot will slow down proportionally to the distance from the endpoint. However, the robot will not slow down past a given minimum speed.
        Parameters:
        maxSpeed - The speed the robot will move/complete the autonomous driving at for the majority of the path.
        slowdownDistance - The distance, in inches, from the endpoint of the autonomous driving at which the robot will begin proportionally slowing down.
        minSpeed - The calculated speed will never be any slower than minSpeed. This is to prevent the robot moving so slowly after the slowdown distance that friction or some other force prevents the robot from fully completing the autonomous path.
        Returns:
        A MovementManner.MovementSpeedSupplier described by the given parameters.
